## script tag
* no need type and language attribute anymore


```js

// an ancient way to hid javascript code form old browsers that didn't know how to process the script tag

<script type="text/javascript"><!--
    ...
//--></script>

```

* If src is set, the script content is ignored.

## External Scripts
* Benefits
  * cache
  * other page that reference the same script will take it from cache instead of downloading
  * reduces traffic and make page faster
* Only simple code put into script tag in html

## Summary
* We can use a <script> tag to add JavaScript code to a page.
* The type and language attributes are not required.
* A script in an external file can be inserted with <script src="path/to/script.js"></script>.
